intOption.toolTip:
Space is allocated in .bitband_ram memory region
 Each byte is also mapped to 8 words in .bitband memory region
 C Example:
 	 // Variable allocated in bitband/bme accessible region (.bitband_ram)
 	 // May be uint8_t, uint16_t or uint32_t
 	 __attribute__ ((section('.bitband_ram')))
 	 uint32_t variable;
 	 // Each word of array maps to an individual bit in bit-band region (.bitband)
 	 __attribute__ ((section('.bitband')))
 	 uint32_t variable_bits[8*sizeof(variable)];
 See bme.h and bitband.h for more information

